Alhassan Bawu, the campaign director of the Labour Party’s (LP) presidential candidate, Peter Obi, in Bauchi State, has defected to the People’s Democratic Party (PDP). Bawu, who dumped the LP alongside other officials of the party in the North-Easst, blamed the Party’s lack of structure at the State, local and ward levels for the decision. He said: “The LP is not strong and won’t be able to win a single seat in the region.’’ READ ALSO: Tinubu Who Served As Governor Is Different Now – PDP Again Picks On His Public Gaffes Announcing his defection to reporters in Bauchi, the capital on Tuesday, he said, “We don’t want to waste our votes and we want to use this time to mobilize votes to who can win the election.’’ He said all the chairmen of the party, state and zonal officers as well as national officers from the zone have also moved to support the PDP’s presidential candidate, Atiku Abubakar.   